On August 13, 2018, the President signed into law H.R. 5515, which authorizes appropriations for fiscal year 2019 for military activities of the Department of Defense, military construction, and defense activities of the Department of Energy. The law also includes provisions for military personnel strengths, recruitment and retention bonuses, special payments, and other authorities relating to the U.S. Armed Forces. It also provides authorities and modifications to national security, foreign affairs, and other related programs.